	"nodes":[
		{"id":"c42b1c02aba5913e","type":"file","file":"Backend intro for presentation.canvas","x":143,"y":-649,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"c098b264db1145c9","type":"text","text":"# # How your backend works\n\nThis matches your **Tech stack ‚Äî backend** slide: how data and server logic run in your app.\n\n---\n\n## The core pipeline\n\n```text\nNext.js App  ‚Üí  Prisma  ‚Üí  Postgres\n   (API)         (ORM)      (database)\n```\n\n| Layer | Role | In your project |\n|-------|------|-----------------|\n| **Next.js App** | Server + API routes | `/api/scenario-chat`, `/api/integrations/plaid/...`, ledger, documents |\n| **Prisma** | Talk to DB in TypeScript | `FinancialEvent`, `Document`, `document_chunks`, `plaid_items` |\n| **Postgres** | Store data | Ledger, uploads metadata, embeddings (pgvector), Plaid tokens |\n\n**Next.js** is frontend *and* backend here ‚Äî API routes under `app/api/` are your backend.\n\n---\n\n## What lives in Postgres\n\n| Data | Table / model |\n|------|----------------|\n| Ledger events | `FinancialEvent` |\n| Extracted obligations | `FinancialObligation` |\n| Cash / user state | `FinancialState` |\n| Uploaded files metadata | `Document` |\n| RAG search | `document_chunks` (+ vector embeddings) |\n| Plaid link | `plaid_items`, `plaid_balance_history` |\n\nOne database = **one financial truth**.\n\n---\n\n## Prisma ‚Äî ‚ÄúRun SQL in JS‚Äù\n\nYou don‚Äôt write raw SQL everywhere. Prisma gives you typed queries:\n\n```typescript\nawait prisma.financialEvent.findMany({ orderBy: { startDate: \"asc\" } });\n```\n\n| Prisma does | You avoid |\n|-------------|-----------|\n| Type-safe queries | Typos in table/column names |\n| Migrations / schema | Hand-editing SQL in prod |\n| Maps to TypeScript types | Guessing DB shape |\n\nSchema: `apps/web/prisma/schema.prisma`  \nClient: `lib/prisma.ts`\n\nVector search (RAG) still uses raw SQL for pgvector ‚Äî Prisma + a bit of SQL where needed.\n\n---\n\n## Two environments (your slide)\n\n```text\nLOCAL                          PRODUCTION\n‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ                          ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ\nDocker Postgres                Neon Postgres (cloud)\n     ‚Üë                              ‚Üë\nnpm run dev                      Vercel deploy\nDATABASE_URL=localhost:5433      DATABASE_URL=neon.tech/...\n```\n\n| | **Local (Docker)** | **Production (Neon)** |\n|---|-------------------|------------------------|\n| **Postgres** | `docker compose up -d postgres` (port **5433**) | Managed Postgres on [Neon](https://neon.tech) |\n| **App** | `npm run dev` ‚Üí localhost:3000 | **Vercel** ‚Üí household-financial-web.vercel.app |\n| **Env** | `DATABASE_URL` in `apps/web/.env` | Same var on Vercel dashboard |\n\nSame **Prisma schema** ‚Äî only the connection URL changes.\n\n---\n\n## Vercel‚Äôs role\n\nVercel hosts the **Next.js app** (not Postgres):\n\n```text\nUser browser\n    ‚Üì\nVercel (Next.js + API routes + SSR)\n    ‚Üì\nNeon Postgres\n    ‚Üì\nVercel Blob (file storage for PDFs)\n```\n\nSecrets (`PLAID_SECRET`, `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `DATABASE_URL`) stay on Vercel ‚Äî never in the browser.\n\n---\n\n## DBeaver ‚Äî database tool\n\n**DBeaver** is for **you**, not the app:\n\n- Connect to Neon or local Postgres  \n- View tables, run SQL  \n- ER diagrams (Prisma Studio lists data but has no diagram)\n\nUseful for debugging: ‚ÄúDid my ledger event save?‚Äù ‚ÄúAre there `document_chunks`?‚Äù\n\n---\n\n## One request example: save ledger event\n\n```text\n1. Telegram or web ‚Üí POST /api/automation/ledger-event\n2. Next.js route.ts (Node on Vercel)\n3. ledger-event.service.ts validates amount, date, category\n4. Prisma ‚Üí INSERT into financial_events\n5. JSON { success: true, data: { reply: \"Saved: ...\" } }\n```\n\nForecast and chat **read** the same tables via Prisma ‚Äî no duplicate spreadsheets.\n\n---\n\n## Backend vs frontend (same repo)\n\n```text\nFRONTEND (.tsx)              BACKEND (.ts)\n‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ               ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ\npages, components            app/api/**/route.ts\nPlaid Link UI                plaid-api.service.ts\nChat form                    scenario-chat/orchestrator.ts\n                             projection.ts (forecast math)\n                                    ‚îÇ\n                                    ‚ñº\n                              Prisma ‚Üí Postgres\n```\n\n---\n\n## 30-second talk track\n\n> The backend is **Next.js API routes** on **Vercel**, talking to **Postgres** through **Prisma**. Locally I use **Docker Postgres**; in production **Neon**. Prisma maps our schema ‚Äî events, documents, Plaid, RAG chunks ‚Äî to TypeScript. **DBeaver** is for inspecting the DB. All money logic and secrets stay on the server; the browser only calls our APIs.\n\n---\n\n## Slide labels (polished)\n\n| Box | Suggested text |\n|-----|----------------|\n| Next.js App | API routes + server logic |\n| Prisma | Type-safe database access |\n| Postgres | Canonical data store |\n| Docker | Local Postgres (dev) |\n| Neon | Cloud Postgres (prod) |\n| Vercel | Hosts Next.js app |\n| DBeaver | DB admin & ER diagrams |\n","x":-920,"y":-900,"width":940,"height":1020}
	],
